    "body" : "@MichaelMyers I just came across a method (of some framework) that accepted an Iterable and turned it into a List, but simply returned the Iterable if it was a List already. What I was looking for, was a method that accepted an array turning it to a mutable List. So turning the array to an immutable List with asList wouldn&#39;t get me any further, but that&#39;s probably a design fault of the method I found."
