    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "Actually, Arrays.asList is <i>not</i> good enough because it doesn&#39;t work on arrays of primitive types. The only built-in way to generically iterate (boxed) elements of primitive types is with reflection, using <code>java.lang.reflect.Array</code>, but its performance is weak. However, you can write your own iterators (or List implementations!) to wrap arrays of primitive types if you want."
