    "comment_id" : 24759580,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "I was looking for this question online. Actually I think it of this way. If the array lends itself to an indexed way of accessing its elements what is the need of an extra iterator? Its waste of work. Simple way of iterating is : for ( int i = 0; i &lt; a.length; i++) a[i]. that&#39;s it. and the best part is you can access any element in O(1)"
  } ],
