    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Unfortunately, arrays aren't '<code>class</code>-enough'.  They don't implement the <code>Iterable</code> interface.</p>\n\n<p>While arrays are now objects that implement Clonable and Serializable, I believe <strong>an array isn't an object in the normal sense</strong>, and doesn't implement the interface.</p>\n\n<p>The reason you can use them in for-each loops is because Sun added in some syntatic sugar for arrays (it's a special case).</p>\n\n<p>Since arrays started out as 'almost objects' with Java 1, it would be far too drastic of a change to make them <em>real</em> objects in Java.</p>\n"
  }, {
