      "comment_id" : 19388439,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "If you&#39;ve got data in an array, it&#39;s possible that you&#39;re doing low-level, performance critical work such as dealing with byte[]&#39;s read from streams. The inability to iterate arrays probably stems from Java generics not supporting primitives as type arguments, as @Gareth says below."
