  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1160081/why-is-an-array-not-assignable-to-iterable",
  "title" : "Why is an array not assignable to Iterable?",
  "body" : "<p>with Java5 we can write:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Foo[] foos = ...\nfor (Foo foo : foos) \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or just using an Iterable in the for loop. This is very handy. </p>\n\n<p>However you can't write a generic method for iterable like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public void bar(Iterable&lt;Foo&gt; foos) { .. }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>and calling it with an array since it is not an Iterable:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Foo[] foos = { .. };\nbar(foos);  // compile time error \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I'm wondering about the reasons behind this design decision.</p>\n"
